This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new model for generative autoencoders. It also involves theoretical and algorithmic extensions to existing work, which is a common theme in machine learning research. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as generative models are often used in AI applications such as image and speech synthesis. 

The paper also involves image datasets such as MNIST and TFD, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The use of gated autoencoders and Markov chains suggests it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as these are common techniques in neural network research. 

Finally, the paper involves generating samples from conditional distributions, which suggests it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as this is a common task in natural language processing.
